- You can have 500 people beating on one mob and not distrupt their casting, have an orc pawn hit YOU and you lose concentration. (not so much now but phear the pawns!!)<br>
<br>
- Caster pets when in your control hit for fairly low ammounts but fast.  When your pet gets charmed look out for those quad 100s (Not sure if this is still true hehe)<br>
<br>
- A green con gnoll can charm a 52 wizard who proceeds to cast Icecomet on a 39 necro with a 2 second cast time.... (Yeah... you know who I mean!!)<br>
<br>
- If I am levitating over the bridge in Nektulos pirahnas can bite me but if I get close to the ground (Take levi off) they can't hit me anymore.<br>
<br>
- A bandit can hit a 60 warlord with full resist gear with spells.  (6 level cap does not apply to them)<br>
<br>
- An un-sowed mob can outrun an outsowed player EVERY time even if it is a blob on the floor.<br>
<br>
- The music of everquest is ruined because we all turn off our music the first time we hear the battle music come up.<br>
(Not really related but bah well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
- Damage caps for melee go up every 10 levels or so for PC's but for NPCs this goes up every level and exponentially.<br>
<br>
- Dot's do full damage on us no matter if we are moving or rooted where our dots to 2/3rds if mob is not stationary.<br>
<br>
- (Here is one not related to mobs)  In PvP caster's spells will do 2/3rds and pets will do 2/3rds damage but Melee's get to hack away unaffected by this phenomenon and love our shoddy ac while sporting resist gear that makes EVERY spell resisted aside from the so called &quot;irresistable&quot; spells which are only resisted half the time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- A level 1 decaying skeleton can resist level 51 splurt.  (Yes... it happened to me, don't ask me why I felt like casting splurt on a decaying skelly hehe)<br>
<br>
- No matter how powerful you are and how scary your pet is orc pawns will attack you when sitting and tell you that you have ruined your lands but you won't ruin theirs.  If you are standing they walk by.<br>
<br>
- The range of distance for caster NPC's spells is double yours.<br>
<br>
- A Healer mob on the floor below you can heal the mob you are killing again and again and again.<br>
<br>
- When a mob dies it spawns back in 6 mins or so whereas if you don't have 512 ram or more you will get killed and spawn back in 8 mins (In kunark only for me for some reason)<br>
<br>
and so on and so on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Oh yeah.  A level 60 cleric player can be taken down by one mob fairly quickly.  A level 60 cleric npc needs a raid force of mass proportions to have a CHANCE to take it down.<br>
<br>
I may have repeated some now that I think of it but this thread is funny for sure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Things I think about when playing but never thought to share it with others... I figured since no one complained it made sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
